MDA (Mail delivery agent):Dovecot, Courier, Cyrus (IMAP/POP3 server)

mailbox formats: mbox or Maildir

IMAP/POP3 are protocols
TELNET is a protocol
SMTP is an application layer protocol, it uses TCP as a transport protocol, IP for routing

MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions): is a standard, allow binary file tobe encoded and sent via SMTP

SMTP port: 25
Ex: use telnet to send mail
-----------------------------------------
famihug@hvn:/var/mail$ telnet localhost 25
Trying ::1...
Connected to localhost.localdomain.
Escape character is '^''.
220 FamiHugK42F ESMTP Postfix (Ubuntu)
	HELO localhost
	250 FamiHugK42F
	MAIL FROM: hvn@familug.com
	250 2.1.0 Ok
	RCPT TO: famihug@hvn.vn
	250 2.1.5 Ok
	DATA
	354 End data with <CR><LF>.<CR><LF>
	Subject: Telnet send mail test   
	hom nay la chu nhat, that la met moi.
	.
	250 2.0.0 Ok: queued as 9082641AB5
	QUIT
	221 2.0.0 Bye
	Connection closed by foreign host.
	'
